  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add your <strong>turkey breast joint[s] </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray, top with a knob of<strong> butter</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 38-45 min or until it's cooked through (when the juices run clear and there's no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Set a timer because your turkey will rest until everything else is ready!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911225902-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911225902-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911225902-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911225902-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911225902-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the turkey is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Strip the <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Tip: Hold the top of the herb sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves</p><p>Slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911235612-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911235612-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911235612-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911235612-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911235612-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Melt 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[40]</span> <strong>butter </strong>in a medium sized pot over a medium heat, then once melted, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped thyme</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, remove the pot from the heat, add the <strong>potato discs</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the potatoes are coated in the butter mixture</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911245417-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911245417-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911245417-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911245417-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911245417-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>buttered potato discs</strong> between 3 holes per person of a muffin tray (or two!)</p><p>Pour over any <strong>remaining butter mixture </strong>and press the potatoes down (reserve the pot)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven and cook for 30 min or until the potatoes are golden and crisp – these are your <strong>pommes Anna</strong></p><p>Tip: No muffin tray? Fill a small oven-proof dish to make one giant pomme Anna!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911259731-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911259731-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911259731-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911259731-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911259731-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, melt a knob of <strong>butter</strong> in the reserved pot over a medium heat</p><p>Add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs, stirring to form a paste</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>red wine paste</strong></p><p>Gradually add the <strong>stock</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped thyme </strong>to the pan and cook for 10-12 min, stirring frequently, until thickened – this is your <strong>thyme gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911275659-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911275659-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911275659-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911275659-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911275659-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spring greens</strong>,<strong> </strong>then rip the leaves off, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Strip your<strong> mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Once the turkey is cooked through, transfer it to a clean chopping board to rest until everything else is ready</p><p>Add any <strong>remaining juices </strong>from the tray to the <strong>thyme gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676911286251-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676911286251-x400.jpg",
